extends ../ui_layout

block content

  .ui.text.container.addBottomMargin
    .ui.raised.segment
      img.ui.medium.image(src='/images/learning_progress_bar.png' style='margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto')
      ul
        li <b>Definition</b>
        ul(style="list-style-type:disc;")
          li <u>Identity theft</u> is when your personal identifiable information (PII) is stolen and used against you.
          li <u>Personal Identifiable Information (PII)</u> is information uniquely associated with you, which can be directly or indirectly used to identify you.
          br
          li Here are some specific examples of PII:
          ul(style="list-style-type:disc;")
            li Name: full name, maiden name, mother’s maiden name, or alias
            li Personal identification numbers: social security number (SSN), passport number, driver’s license number, taxpayer identification number, patient identification number, financial account number, or credit card number
            li Personal address information: street address, or email address
            li Personal telephone numbers
      .ui.one.column.centered.grid(style="margin: 50px")
        .ui.large.pointing.below.circular.label(style="float: left;")
            p(style="padding: 10px") Key concept here is 
              b Personal Identifiable Information (PII)
        img.ui.small.image.right.floated(src='/images/avatar-pic.png' style="float: right")
      .div(style='margin-top:80px;')
        button.ui.medium.button.left.floated(onclick="location.href='/identity_learn_page1';") 
          i.arrow.left.icon 
          | Back
        button.ui.medium.button.left.floated(onclick="location.href='/';") Save & Exit
        button.ui.medium.button.right.floated(onclick="location.href='/identity_learn_page4';")
          | Next
          i.arrow.right.icon



